Package com.stephengware.java.ai.planning.logic

Contains objects for representing logical formulas.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Bindings
    A data structure which tracks constraints on the values of variables.
    Expression
    An expression is any logical formula with a truth value.
    Formula
    The parent class of all logical formulas.
    Literal
    A literal is an atomic expression (i.e.
    Substitution
    A substitution specifies that certain terms should be replaced by other terms.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BooleanExpression
    A boolean expression is an expression composed of other expressions and combined according to certain rules.
    Conjunction
    A conjunction is a Boolean expression that is true when all of its conjuncts are true.
    Constant
    A constant is a term which represents one specific object in the world.
    Disjunction
    A disjunction is a Boolean expression that is true when any of its disjuncts are true.
    ExpressionObject
    An implementation of Expression which provides a default implementation of Object.equals(Object).
    HashBindings
    An implementation of the Bindings data structure based on a hash table, which allows fast lookups but is costly to clone and modify.
    HashSubstitution
    A substitution which uses a HashMap to keep track of substitutions.
    ListBindings
    An implementation of the Bindings data structure based on a linked list, which is easy to clone and modify but provides slower lookups.
    NAryBooleanExpression
    The parent class of all Boolean expressions with an arbitrary number of arguments.
    NegatedLiteral
    The negation of a literal is a literal.
    Negation
    A negation is a Boolean expression which represents the opposite of some expression.
    Predication
    Represents a single statement in function-free predicate logic.
    Term
    Terms represent objects in the world.
    Variable
    A variable represents a placeholder for a constant whose value is not yet known.
